rComments: Professor Shvarts is an amazing professor. His lectures are entertaining & engaging, though his tests are challenging but he gave the short answer questions in advance, which was helpful. This course is content heavy - get ready to memorize 40 pages of notes for the midterm. Nonetheless, I had a great experience and I'd recommend this course.

He was easy to understand. Lectures were clear, he didn't use too many big words you wouldn't understand. He encouraged you to visit him during office hours. Reading was good, I did good in his class. I'm sure you will too.

As an Alumni, Professor Shvarts is probably one of the only professors I will always remember. He is an amazing professor - very approachable and will do his best to help you in any way he can. He makes the lectures so interesting, I still remember some of the concepts I learned in his class. Plus, he is superrrr cute
amazing n cute

Late for class most of the time (up to 40 minutes). Rude when you email him. Totally arrogant, and acts like he's better than you. Unapproachable. Marking is very tough and he is not willing to discuss it with you. Highly judgmental. Class was a bunch of readings, and he basically read notes of the readings off of a slide. Incredibly boring.
He is the best professor ever. Take him!
He is amazing and funny! Love his class, he is one of the best profs I ever had!! Not to mention how amazing and interesting his lectures are!

Shvarts is an okay prof. His lectures are basically where he reads the slides to you (add on a few jokes here and there), so they're boring and not necessary. Gives SA test questions in advance, but MC is quite difficult (even T/F are difficult). His TAs marked very subjectively. Although he was helpful, they were useless and rude.
He is a very interesting Prof talks alot about the Russian Mafia. you don;t really need to put effort in his class before passing
Took it in summer. He's a really good prof. His lectures are really interesting though it may have its dull moments. The videos he shows are really interesting. He'll make you engaged
THIS PROFF IS AMAZING ... THE WORK LOAD IS HEAVY BUT HE'LL MAKE YOU WANT TO READ AND WATCH THE EXTRA VIDEOS

No words can describe how good of a prof he is. Gives a review of the test & exam before hand & even gave away some questions that were going to be asked. He's very nice to look at & makes jokes when he's lecturing, so it's a very interesting class you won't fall asleep in!

This guy is an awesome professor. I didn't want to take SOC209 but now that I have, I'm SO glad that I did. He's helpful, funny, interesting, and makes the exams and assignments so straight forward for you. Overall, he's an awesome prof. I have almost a 90 in the class right now.

I love him. That sums it up. He is so funny and witty and sarcastic, it makes the experience so amazing. I'm taking other soc courses, just bc he's teaching them. His lectures are based on readings, so you don't have to do them and he tells you EVERYTHING on midterms!
Interesting, not the greatest prof ever but definitely one of the better ones. if you do and understand your readings, you can get a good grade. easy to listen to, engaging.

You can't fall asleep in his class because he's good at teaching.  His slides make sense and he teaches what's on the test or exam.  Do all your readings and know the slides.  Some of the readings are irrelevant but interesting anyway.
Was an extremely hard marker, found out he gives his TA's the marking scheme so it is not their fault. Requires very detailed answers and you don't get the mark if you miss a portion of the sentence.
class had no concept, bunch of readings put together

Amazing prof! very clear lecture slides and clealy explains each slide with funny and engaging commentary. He outlines exactly which slides will be on exam and is very approchable. HIGHLY recommended!! Just a nice person and enjoyable lecture. I took it in the summer.

very hot and very interesting.witty and kept the class engaging which for a summer course was great. his TA's marked super hard though and towards the end though he rushed a bit overall i'd definetely do another course of his.
